<plot>This summer replacement comedy/variety show, not to be confused with the long-running sitcom, was a simultaneous parody of/homage to the 1930's. In addition to its regular cast of comedians, each week's program featured appearances by one of the top big bands of the era (Benny Goodman, Duke Ellington, and Buddy Rich all appeared on the program).</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?229544</url></doc>
